The Help Scout MCP server allows AI assistants to interact with your Help Scout data, including inboxes, conversations, customers, and organizations. It enables searching tickets, retrieving thread history, and summarizing conversations directly from your editor or chat window [1][2].

To set up the server in your MCP client configuration (e.g., Claude Desktop), use the following structure:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "helpscout": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["help-scout-mcp-server"],
      "env": {
        "HELPSCOUT_APP_ID": "your-app-id",
        "HELPSCOUT_APP_SECRET": "your-app-secret"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

Key tools include searchConversations for filtered ticket lists, comprehensiveConversationSearch for keyword lookups, structuredConversationFilter for specific ticket IDs, and getConversationSummary for quick previews [3][4]. The server automatically discovers your inboxes upon connection [1][5]. Requirements include Node.js 18+ and a Help Scout OAuth2 App [3][6].
